                            <comment id="421337" author="pjones" created="Wed, 17 Jul 2024 18:45:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Believed to be duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17525&quot; title=&quot;Unaligned DIO interop with different page sizes fails&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17525&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17525&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="406968" author="adilger" created="Sat, 9 Mar 2024 19:18:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this interop issue will be fixed via Shaun&apos;s patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/53997&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/53997&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17525&quot; title=&quot;Unaligned DIO interop with different page sizes fails&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17525&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17525&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: unaligned DIO iterop page alignment&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="406015" author="adilger" created="Fri, 1 Mar 2024 22:39:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Patrick, could you please take a look at this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It appears the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13805&quot; title=&quot;i/o path: Unaligned direct i/o&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13805&quot;&gt;LU-13805&lt;/a&gt; llite: Implement unaligned DIO connect flag&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; patch has broken interop for ldiskfs servers rather than fixed it.  I&apos;m not totally sure why, but it might be that setting &quot;&lt;tt&gt;data-&amp;gt;ocd_connect_flags2 |= OBD_CONNECT2_UNALIGNED_DIO&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is done when it is too late to have any affect on the client (e.g. it isn&apos;t saved in the OSC import that is checked later?).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The testing pretty clearly shows that the issue started on 2023-11-18 when that patch landed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=e1b4c5d2-90fc-11e2-8311-52540035b04c&amp;amp;start_date=2023-11-01&amp;amp;end_date=2024-01-01&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=e1b4c5d2-90fc-11e2-8311-52540035b04c&amp;amp;start_date=2023-11-01&amp;amp;end_date=2024-01-01&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
